First create new user for AMON:

$ mysql -u root -p [-h hostname]
> CREATE USER 'amonusername'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'yourpassword';
(Replace 'localhost' with 'hostname' if MySQL is not running on
you local machine)

Then create AMON DBs and grant access for AMON user:
> CREATE DATABASE AMON_test1;
> CREATE DATABASE AMON_test2;
> GRANT ALL ON AMON_test1.* TO 'amonusername'@'localhost';
> GRANT ALL ON AMON_test2.* TO 'amonusername'@'localhost';

There are 2 SQL scripts:

1) db_build.sql is a script that creates AMON_test1 database for archival data

2) db_mc_build.sql is a script that creates AMON_test2 database for MC data

To run the SQL scripts, use:

mysql -u amonusername [-h hostname] -p AMON_test1 < db_build.sql
mysql -u amonusername [-h hostname] -p AMON_test2 < db_mc_build.sql
(You can drop -h if host is localhost)

Attention: by running these two scripts on db.hpc.rcc.psu.edu you will erase current AMON
databases. Use these scripts to create databases on your own machine (i.e. localhost).
